#: ../../../about.md:1
msgid "About"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about.md:3
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about.md:5
msgid ""
"The Visualization Toolkit (VTK) is a robust and open-source software system "
"that provides advanced features in 3D computer graphics, image processing, "
"modeling, volume rendering, and scientific visualization. It offers threaded "
"and distributed-memory parallel processing for scalability and better "
"performance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about.md:11
msgid ""
"VTK is a cross-platform library that can run on many operating systems, "
"including Windows, macOS, Linux, and even the web and mobile devices."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about.md:14
msgid ""
"VTK is widely used in both academic and commercial settings, as well as in "
"government institutions such as Los Alamos National Lab and CINECA. The "
"software was originally published in the textbook titled \"The Visualization "
"Toolkit, an Object-Oriented Approach to 3D Graphics\" and has grown "
"significantly since its release in 1994 with an extensive worldwide user "
"base."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about.md:20
msgid ""
"VTK maintains a high-quality software process, which includes CMake, CTest, "
"CDash, and CPack. The software is written in C++ with additional language "
"bindings to reach a broader audience, with an excellent interoperability "
"with Python."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about.md:25
msgid ""
"As open source software, VTK is free to use for any purpose. Technically, "
"VTK has a BSD-style license, which imposes minimal restrictions for both "
"open and closed source applications."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about.md:29
msgid ""
"If you're interested in exploring the growth and usage patterns of VTK, we "
"provide you with our statistics. The statistics are available on Open Hub, a "
"platform focused on community-driven software, and PyPI stats, which "
"provides download statistics for VTK packages. By analyzing these "
"statistics, you can gain insights into the community's size, VTK's adoption "
"rates, and popularity. Check out the links below for more information:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about.md:35
msgid "[Open Hub](https://www.openhub.net/p/vtk)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about.md:36
msgid "[PyPI stats](https://pypistats.org/packages/vtk)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about.md:38
msgid "Features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about.md:40
msgid ""
"VTK provides a comprehensive set of features that support visualization, "
"modeling, and data analysis. Here are some highlights:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about.md:45
msgid "Filters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about.md:46
msgid ""
"VTK's filter-based architecture processes data by transforming and "
"manipulating it through a pipeline of successive filters. This approach "
"produces derived data that can be rendered using VTK's graphics system. "
"Filters can be combined into a dataflow network, which enables a flexibly "
"configurable workflow."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about.md:52
msgid "Graphics System"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about.md:53
msgid ""
"VTK provides a sophisticated rendering abstraction layer over the underlying "
"graphics library (OpenGL with experimental support for WebGL), simplifying "
"the creation of engaging visualizations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about.md:58
msgid "Data Model"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about.md:59
msgid ""
"VTK’s core data model has the ability to represent almost any real-world "
"problem related to physical science. The fundamental data structures are "
"particularly well-suited to medical imaging and engineering work that "
"involves finite difference and finite element solutions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about.md:65
msgid "Data Interaction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about.md:66
msgid ""
"VTK provides several tools for interactive data exploration and analysis, "
"including 3D widgets, interactors, and 2D widget libraries integration like "
"Qt. These enable powerful user interaction capabilities, making it easier to "
"understand the content, shape, and meaning of data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about.md:72
msgid "2D Plots and Charts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about.md:73
msgid ""
"VTK supports a full set of 2D plot and chart types for tabular data "
"visualization. It also includes picking and selection capabilities, allowing "
"users to query data interactively. VTK's excellent interoperability with "
"Python and Matplotlib further increases its flexibility."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about.md:79
msgid "Parallel Processing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about.md:80
msgid ""
"VTK offers excellent support for scalable distributed-memory parallel "
"processing under MPI. VTK filters implement finer-grained parallelism using "
"vtkSMP for coarse-grained threading and viskores for fine-grained processing "
"on many-core and GPU architectures. These parallel processing capabilities "
"make VTK highly efficient and suited for processing large data sets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about.md:88
msgid "License"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../about.md:90
msgid ""
"VTK is distributed under the OSI-approved BSD 3-clause License. See [here]"
"(https://gitlab.kitware.com/vtk/vtk/-/blob/master/Copyright.txt) for details."
msgstr ""

